# Supabase & application boundaries (DDD style)

## Objective

Postgres / Auth / Supabase Storage are **implementation details backing the Next.js app**, **not** a public backend reachable by shortcuts from arbitrary layers/tools. Reads and writes meaningful to the business traverse **server actions, route handlers, Server Components**, and adapters under `src/lib/`, obeying **`03-architecture.mdc`** (pure core without network plumbing) plus **`04-security.mdc`**.

## What qualifies as illicit “direct access” (forbidden unless exceptions listed below)

1. **Instantiating Supabase clients anywhere other than `src/lib/supabase/`** — Never add `createBrowserClient`, `createServerClient`, or `createClient` from `@supabase/ssr` / `@supabase/supabase-js` inside components, hooks, `src/lib/<domain>/`, or miscellaneous paths. The **only** allowed location for factories + cookie/header wiring remains **`src/lib/supabase/`** (e.g. `client.ts`, `server.ts`, `admin.ts`, `middleware.ts`). Other code receives an injected client or invokes exported wrappers from that folder.

2. **Manual REST calls against Supabase** (`*.supabase.co/rest/v1/…`, `auth/v1`, etc.) inside `src/` for business payloads — Prefer the SDK/canonical adapters; duplicated `fetch` to PostgREST requires an ADR justifying extremes (integrations outside runtime).

3. **Parallel JDBC/Raw Postgres / `supabase db` substitutes for domain workflows** — Product code shouldn’t bypass Supabase pooled access for writes/reads mirrored by runtime features. Exceptions: **`supabase/migrations/`**, seeds, and documented ops tasks (bootstrap schema)—not substitutes for domain server actions.

4. **Throwaway scripts using `service_role` against prod** orchestrating canonical business workflows (signup, tuition, imports) **without** the validation/RLS/audit/analytics present in **`08-analytics-observability.mdc`**. Incident-only exceptions remain **explicitly documented** (runbooks/ADR **`10`**).

## Acceptable approaches (still not “illegal shortcuts”)

- Import **`type`**-only aliases from `@supabase/supabase-js` (`import type { SupabaseClient }`) for domain/tests when the boundary injects implementations.
- Build clients **only** in **`src/lib/supabase/**` centralizing browser/server/admin factories + env (`publicEnv`, …).
- SQL migrations/RLS under `supabase/migrations/` express persistence contracts — application usage still crosses app surfaces.
- Supabase dashboards / exploratory SQL strictly for troubleshooting or irregular ops—not default business ingress; governance applies if changes become persistent.

## Layer relationship (DDD)

- **Ports** — outward APIs are server actions / routes exposing use cases.
- **Adapters** — `src/lib/` (especially `supabase`) translate those ports to Supabase.
- **Pure domain** modules (`src/lib/<context>/` with **no Supabase**) hold testable logic; orchestration pulls from hooks/actions/handlers instead.

## Agent checklist

- [ ] Creating **new Supabase factories** → only **`src/lib/supabase/`** with existing patterns reused.
- [ ] Hook/component importing `@supabase/ssr|supabase-js` to instantiate clients → **lift** boundary or reuse browser singleton.
- [ ] Seeing `fetch` to Supabase project URLs → replace with adapters unless ADR’d.
- [ ] Surfacing sensitive auth/data/contracts → satisfy **`10-engineering-governance.mdc`**.
